name: Katelyn Sergi
bio:
Hey MAMA!
Sharing daily IMPERFECT mom & wife life
Mommy to Rhett (5) 💙, Capri (2) 💗, Blakely (6m) 💗

social_posts.post_text: Breakfast with Santa this morning. Rhett was more interested in the lights outside and Capri wanted nothing to do with the jolly old man. But hey, Rhett let him know he wanted a pencil case for Christmas... we called that a win. 🎅

Cookie baking crew 🍪 Found out the little ones like cookie dough more than the cookies themselves.... just like mama. 🙃

We’ve been stuck inside all day because of the cold...but we got most of the cleaning done, lots of laundry completed, and are fixing homemade queso.

I still have quite a few presents to wrap tonight.... eek. Tell me I’m not the only one who waited until last minute?! 🤪

PS- no worries.. Ross is right behind them, ducking under the counter to make sure they’re safe!

2023 - the year we become a family of 5!

Hope you all had a sweet New Year. When I was a kiddo, my family always went to dinner and dessert on New Years Day. 

I want to continue that tradition with our babes. We went to our favorite local Irish restaurant and ended the evening with ice cream. 

My goal for this year is to show up on this platform more.  Can you believe I’ve been “blogging” for 6.5 years?! 

Send me all your requests for content as I refresh the brand and continue on this amazing journey. Thank you for all of your support and love... I’m so glad to be here with you. 💖

Took the baby out dancing last night.👶🏻

So proud of Ross and all of his accomplishments. It’s not always easy being a firefighter wife... but we sure are thankful for all that you do.

PS- tried @lawless gloss in Daisy Pink ... 10/10 recommend

Valentines Day gift idea 💗... a marriage toolkit! The marriage toolkit from @SoulRefiner is quite simply dreamy. It has a variety of books, games, manuals, and sweet little notes that center around guiding your marriage through faith. (If you swipe left, I placed a sample of my favorites out for you to see.)

Ross is a charmer. He always has been. He leaves all the notes, buys all the flowers, and makes all dinners - just because. I’m so happy to have these cards so I can return the favor. 

One of the games in the kit suggested making one of Ross’ favorite foods - chicken bacon ranch bake - coming right up!  And when it’s his turn.. I’ll take his famous biscuits and gravy. 

 If you’re looking for an idea for vday, the marriage toolkit is it!  You can get 20% off with the code “Kate” during checkout. Marriagetoolkit.com/katesnumberones

Turned 33 on Sunday! 🎂 And, I have a bday present request... HELP US FIGURE OUT A BOY AND GIRL NAME... 🥰

We have ideas, but it’s not as definite as Rhett and Capri were.  We will take all the name advice!

My fam made me feel super special on my birthday. Ross tried taking me on a date night in the evening... but mama got the stomach bug. Dehydration led my body into having contractions for hours. It was the most horrible feeling.. and so scary.

However... baby is doing great! .. and we’re hoping to save the next contractions for April! :)

Leave your name suggestions below!

Spunky, sweet, and almost two years old. ✌🏻

Current favorites:
Food: sweets & blueberries
Animal: dogs (although, they are NOT allowed to be anywhere close)
Toy: her babies
Color: pink
Word: “otay”
Song: Bluey theme song

Loves to have her hair brushed, copy everything Rhett does, sing songs as loud as she can, and give constant hugs 🤗 

PS:  no worries - Dad and big bro were right behind the counter making sure their sweet little Pri didn’t try anything crazy.💗
I’ve waited for this my whole life...

WATER BROKE! Let’s have a baby!!💙💗

Final guesses on whether it’s a girl or boy?!

#40weekspregnant

Our very first picture together. A picture that  encapsulates a mother’s love.

Our baby GIRL arrived last night - on her due date.  We’ve gone through a lot together in this less than 24 hour period, but we’re both happy and healthy now!

Can you believe it?.... ANOTHER BABY GIRL! 💙💓💓

It’s a GIRL! Blakely Hart - you make us the happiest big family of five. 

We are finally home from the hospital and tonight was our first night all together. Rhett and Capri are SO in love.

Capri is VERY territorial and wants to hold her at all times. Rhett kept singing something along the lines of, “You are surrounded by love - I just love her.  Blakely you are surrounded by love”.

I’d say we’re all pretty smitten over here. Cheers to newborn livin’ - full of nursing sessions, QVC purchases, and all the food.

Five days postpartum 👶🏻

The recovery has been the best of all three (still hard), but the birth itself has been my toughest experience. *I’ll share more about that at some point.*

Even being on my third round of postpartum... the nights are still long, the recovery is still a process, and the tears still come and go. 

....but the happiness, joy, and gratitude of this sweet blessing outshines everything else.  Our fam is so grateful for a new little sis to love & adore forever. 

If you’re newly postpartum, you aren’t alone.  YOU are a great mom!  I’m rooting for you!! 

#newlypostpartum #postpartum #postpartumlife #motherhood #fourthtrimester

FIVE!!!! He’s a constant joker, a sweet sweet soul, and as thoughtful as can be - just like his daddy.

I got so many messages from you all this week about how you started following this page around the time Rhett was born! Can you believe it’s been five years?! Thank you for following along all this time. It means so much!

For Rhett’s birthday he requested pizza, cake, balloons, and going outside... so that’s just what we did.

In his own words, it was the “best birthday ever”.

We love you sweet dude. Happy birthday!!

How we chose her name:  Blakely

You know in high school how we used to doodle our name with our boyfriend’s last name? That’s what I used to do with my future baby names too. 🥰 Anyone else?

I had pages upon pages of “Blakely” in colorful drawings and cute fonts. ( I SO wish I still had one of those journals.)

When I mentioned the name to Ross as a possible girl name, he absolutely loved it too.  If we had a girl, Blakely she would be.

After I revealed her name to my high school friends, they all responded with something along the lines of “You got your Blakely”.

I sure did. And we’re so thankful. 💗

Life lately ☁️ 

I’m a mama to THREE BABIES... what?!?! 💙💗💗 I can’t count how many times a day I think about how grateful I am to be their mom.

Being postpartum, I also have moments during the day where I feel super overwhelmed, anxious, or worried. 

Postpartum is weird and wonderful and hard and beautiful and overwhelming and peaceful.... it’s so many feelings.

On a side note - if you watched my stories - you saw I somehow hurt my neck/shoulders while breastfeeding. 🤪 I’ve been in bed the past two days - unable to move much at all. A few of you messaged me saying it happened to you too.  From here on out, I’m working on proper posture during nursing sessions. This cannot happen again, haha. 

Linking my bright and cozy sweat set in stories!  If the stories are expired comment on here or message me and I’ll send you the link!

She’s my mini in so many ways. 

We love ourselves some candy.
Sleeping in is quite luxurious.
We’d simply rather be carried from one place to another.
We’ll do it all ourselves though.
Pink blush is the best blush - unless it’s a palette of multi colors - then we like that one. 
Reading books every day is good for our hearts.
Did we mention we like to eat?
Going on adventures is our favorite.
We sometimes freeze in awkward situations.
We enjoy writing and drawing using our huge pen collection.
We like sparkles.
Pushing down the buttons on fountain drinks is necessary.
Putting things back in their spots and keeping organized is also needed.
Singing and dancing make us happy.
Family time is the best time. 
And.... We kinda look alike. :)

Slide left to see a photo of mini Kate at the same age. 

#motherhood #momlife #familyof5 #motherhoodjourney

“Baby, we got a girl!”

#genderreveal #genderrevealvideos #motherhood #momlife #pregnancy

Little miss cupcake is a month old (okay, six weeks 🥰). 

She’s our miss go with the flow, loves being outside, sleeps fairly well, just started cooing, wants all the cuddles, sweet baby girl.

We’re so thankful for you, Blakely Hart. 💗
Best friends forever 🤍

It was a good day.

Farmers market, splash pad, naps, and a concert in the park 

Ross and I were just talking about how hard parenting can be - as we had three little ones all yelling about  different things while we were driving in the car.

Hard.... & also the privilege of our lives. 
👶🏻👶🏻👶🏻

We’re in our parenting little ones era and so thankful for it. ❤️

Blakely is two months old! ✌🏻 

And when you’re the third child... apparently you do not get your own monthly photos. That’s okay - they’re three times as cute. 🥰

She’s a smiley sweet little thing. She’s cooing and holds her head high.  Blakely looooves getting attention from her bro and sis & will instantly smile when she sees them. 

Just like Rhett, she stares at spinning fans and the big fake fiddle leaf tree in our family room, ha!

Current baby favorites:
Baby blanket @halosleep 
Baby wash and lotion @earthmamaorganics 
Onesie @oldnavy 
Pacifiers @philipsavent 
Stroller @zoestrollers & @babyjogger 
Nighttime monitor @owletcare 
Bottles @comotomobaby
7 years of marriage and 3 babies later...❤️ I love this life with you. Happy anniversary AND Father’s Day, Ross. Our love story is my favorite.

Some days I want time to hurry so I can see who she’ll be. Other days I’m in disbelief she’s already two months old.

Taking in the now and all her sweet little smiles. She’s the happiest little thing, loves to coo, and is going with the flow of having two siblings who are always busy. 🙃

Outfit is from @shopcrankypeach on Etsy! 

1:  Blakely at two months
2:  Capri at four months
Seventeen year old me would be happy to know this is where it all led to.

Spent the most beautiful morning picking flowers with the kiddos. 🌸 

The first ones we saw were snapdragons and I instantly thought of my grandma.

I remember spending summer days opening the little dragon mouths and thinking they were the coolest flowers ever. My grandma would always smile and pretend to be as enamored as I was with them.  Every time I see them, it makes me think of her. 

Thankful for these summer days with my babies. 💙💗💗

Wherever she moved, they were always right there. ☀️
.
.
.
Motherhood, mom life, mom of three

Powered by Diet Coke as of late. 

Started a new job this week and Blakely is beginning to wake up throughout the night again. 

Around four months is when both Rhett and Capri began waking often. 

Sooooo… we will see if the up all night trend continues. 😴

In the meantime, I’ll take chocolate, Big Brother Live, and a little caffeine.

I feel as if I’ve known her forever, but also catch myself marveling at her newness.

Almost didn’t post this because my postpartum hair loss is coming in hot. 

But… I decided to be vulnerable and do it anyway in hopes that another mom going through it feels seen.

Losing your hair after all the body changes you’ve already been through isn’t the most fun part of postpartum, but the hair loss is only temporary.

And loving you is forever, Miss Blakely.

They’ve taught me more in these past 5 years than I’ve learned the previous 28. 

Rhett has taught me to laugh, to be silly, to always be empathetic, to do what’s right even when it’s difficult, to show up often when it comes to friendships, and to have fun - even in the mundane.

Capri has a very similar personality to me and phew it’s grounding. She’s sassy and she’s sweet. She’s taught me to remember who I was and what I needed when I was a little girl. She’s taught me to be understanding, to be goofy, to stay carefree, and to take chances.

Blakely has taught me to soak it all in, to enjoy the little things, to remember how comforting a small cuddle can be for anyone - no matter your size. 

All three have taught me that I will have many titles in life… but my favorite of all the titles will always be… “mom”.
Apple cider slushies, apple doughnuts, sunflower fields, hay rides, and now.. nap time for all of us. ☺️🌻

Blakey gurllllll. 

She’s five months and so so sweet. She did not go through the four month sleep regression like Rhett and Capri did. Whattttt?!

That has historically been the hardest sleeping month for us.  Like, I’m talking up 7 or 8 times a night sleep regression. 

Rhett started sleeping in his crib around 6 months and Capri started sleeping in hers around 6 and 1/2 months.

Since Blakely is probably (still figuring that one out) our last baby… I can’t seem to come to terms with her sleeping in another room next month. 😢

Both Rhett and Capri started sleeping better when in their own rooms, but… ugh this momma’s heart struggled then and I know will struggle now.

However, Blakely is a very light sleeper so even little noises when we’re getting ready, opening a drawer, or getting out of bed may wake her up. I know she’ll be ready in a few months but the thought of it… 🥲

When did your babies start sleeping in their own space?!
He was truly meant to be their big brother.  He’s sweet , gentle, a leader, and always keeps us laughing. You are the greatest, Roo.

Polo games have become a recent summer tradition. 🐎 We watch the horses, enjoy a picnic, and spend the entire time making sure the kids don’t run onto the field, ha.

There’s also a flyover during halftime that drops candy…. It’s the kids’ favorite part of the night. 

Can’t wait until next Summer, @hickoryhallpoloclub 💗

“I know we’re tired right now, but one day we’ll laugh about it.” This song has me 🥹. 

 We’ve done all the fall things and we.are.tired.

Tired, but full of joy and gratitude. Seeing their faces light up and create core memories makes me create core memories of their happiness. And that… that’s my favorite. 💗

In the “you haven’t had a full night’s sleep in over six months, doing all the fun activities, always calming feelings, healing boo boos with a kiss, loving them so much your heart can hardly hold it together” era. Anyone else? 🥰

Hulk did not care that it was snowing outside. He was going to go to EVERY house in the neighborhood. :) Our unicorns however, were more interested in that cozy lifestyle of cuddles and warm temps. 

It’s so fun being their mom. 💙💗💗

There is a mother somewhere … words I needed when I first became a mom, words I need to hear now, and words I’ll need to hear in the future.

As mothers we are all on different journeys, but in the different journeys we find solidarity and empathy for one another no matter which stage we’re in.

Grateful that God gave me three beautiful souls to raise, teach, and most importantly…  love. 

Which part of this hit home for you??
Her first word…. Mama 💗
God gave us three beautiful babies.  Thankful doesn’t even begin to describe it. 👶🏻👶🏻👶🏻

A joyful weekend of Christmas parades and Christmas trains. 

Have I mentioned lately how much I love being their mom? 😊

Ross and Rhett match and I think that’s one of my favorite things about the first picture.

Our little guy had his Christmas program the other night and he sure shined. 

This is my first experience as a mom to see my oldest love in a school program. 

….and I cried. And probably always will to be honest.

ITS JUST SO SWEET!

THE BEST SANTA!!!! He had my mom and I in tears with his sweet compliments about what a great big brother Rhett was. 

Rhett told the jolly ole guy he wanted surprises while Capri spent her time trying to convince Santa himself that she was actually Santa….. (see the video). 🥹 

Blakely was in awe of all the lights and decorations.

I love these moments with them.
POV: Christmas time is even more wonderful when you have three babies to love.
